entries.meaning: (gerund of pluck) An act in which something is plucked.
A fragment of something obtained by plucking.
examples: Yield per acre and moisture content of grass pluckings taken at 14- or 28-day intervals during the seasons of 1933 and 1934

entries.meaning: (printing) The undesirable situation in which printed ink becomes detached from the paper.
